Chief Executive Officer of Monimichelle Group, Ebi Egbe has congratulated Remo Stars  after securing a continental ticket as curtain was drawn on the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL). Remo over the weekend defeated Niger Tornadoes by 3-0 to finish third on the NPFL log, thus securing ticket to play in the CAF Confederation Cup. Interestingly, the Ikenne Warriors only made their debut in the top flight this season.   WAFCON 2022: Depleted Super Falcons fall to Morocco in semis     Aribo happy with life at Saints     Rodgers reveals return date for injured Ndidi   Speaking on the feat, Egbe said he was  proud of Remo Stars and the club president, Kunle Soname who he described as one who has a lot of passion for the round leather game. Egbe whose outfit constructed Remo’s Ikenne stadium turf noted that given the state of the art turf Remo play on at home, the performance of the club is not coming as a surprise. “I congratulate them and I am happy Monimichelle is part of the club’s success story just like Enyimba.”